               <H2>Market Summary</H2>
               <p>Hazeldean Mall is the only enclosed shopping centre in Kanata. The Centre has been recently upgraded inside
and out including a new food court, fountain/water feature, exterior signage and all new entrances.</p>
            <p>Ottawa is one of the country’s largest consumer markets with retail sales per capita sitting in third place among
Canada’s metro areas of 1 million or more. The Conference Board of Canada forecasted that retail sales in
Ottawa would exceed $13.5 billion. In the past 10 years Ottawa has surpassed both Toronto and Montreal in
retail sales growth with a staggering surge of 70%. Ottawa’s location between the two largest retail markets in
Canada, Toronto and Montreal, has allowed its consumers to be influenced by “big-city” retail sophistication. The
result being the opportunity for more, varied and sophisticated retailers to enter the market.</p>
               <br>
